JsonTypeInfo<T>`. The actual API is `options.GetTypeInfo(typeof(T))` which returns a non-generic `JsonTypeInfo`, and there's also `TryGetTypeInfo` for safer lookups. Since the user wants to avoid casting to get `JsonTypeInfo<T>`, I should just test this in a .NET 11 project to see if a generic overload exists or find the cleanest workaround available.","outputTokens":1472,"requestId":"6C02:180764:11A663:173708:69FFD72E"},"id":"20554525-009a-49c9-ad26-a50ecb9194d4","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:36.817Z","parentId":"12cd6b14-eb28-4939-828d-5d7b5be1b623"}
